TITLE: "Dricus Du Plessis calls out Khamzat Chimaev for future fight"
AUTHOR: Aaron Case, Yardbarker
DESCRIPTION: When Khamzat Chimaev broke Robert Whittaker’s jaw while submitting him in their middleweight bout on Saturday at UFC 308, he declared himself past due for a title fight. Current middleweight champion Dricus Du Plessis wholeheartedly agreed with the now 14-0 Chimaev.

DESCRIPTION: The seventh-year receiver will finish his 2024 campaign with 25 receptions for 320 yards and a touchdown.

TITLE: "Oregon still No.1, Miami climbs to No.5"
AUTHOR: The Associated Press
DESCRIPTION: Miami edged ahead of Texas and climbed to No. 5 in The Associated Press Top 25 college football poll on Sunday, its highest ranking since 2017, and Notre Dame, BYU and Texas A&M all moved into the top 10.The post Oregon still No.1, Miami climbs to No.5 appeared first on The Tribune.
